<ul>
<li>Notes: 4 tables, each table 4 papers x 15 minutes + 30 min discussion. Each of 3 Co-Chairs (+John Traxler) leads a table that are grouped around the <a href="http://cloudworks.ac.uk/cloud/view/8501" target="_blank">Symposium Call themes</a>, kicking off with our own paper. 30 minutes report back from the tables by lead person. See <a href="http://cloudworks.ac.uk/cloud/view/8616" target="_blank">how to present during a roundtable</a></li>
<li>
<div>Round table 1. Focus on new patterns of connected social learning and work-based practices (Chair JC)</div>
</li>
<ul>
<li><a href="http://tinyurl.com/p9sez8a" target="_blank">John Cook</a>&nbsp;- <a href="http://cloudworks.ac.uk/cloud/view/8586" target="_blank">User Generated Contexts: Thinking about changes in mass communication in terms of agency, innovation, trust and risk</a></li>
<li>
<p id="docs-internal-guid-2362c218-4460-8550-e025-3bdaf05c50e7" style="line-height: 1.15; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;" dir="ltr">Bernhard Gross - <a href="http://cloudworks.ac.uk/cloud/view/8614" target="_blank">Journalist, citizen and learner? &mdash; A consideration of context in learning mobile journalism through mobile learning</a></p>
</li>
<li>
<p id="docs-internal-guid-2362c218-4460-8550-e025-3bdaf05c50e7" style="line-height: 1.15; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;" dir="ltr">David Barber: <a href="http://cloudworks.ac.uk/cloud/view/8599" target="_blank">Keep Taking the Tablets: Integrating the Mobile in Work-Based Learning</a></p>
</li>
</ul>
<li>
<div>Round table 2.Focus on designing for &lsquo;mobile learning&rsquo; at scale (Chair&nbsp;YM)</div>
