              <title>Jonathan Vernon : A Virtual Companion for Swimming Coaches</title>
              <link>https://cloudworks.ac.uk/cloud/view/7256</link>
              <guid>https://cloudworks.ac.uk/cloud/view/7256</guid>
              <description><![CDATA[Poolside with 16 - 40 swimmers you need eyes in the back of your head to monitor each swimmer, keep tabs on a programme, monitor what is going on and take on board and apply a myriad of new techniques and approaches. A Google headset may be the answer - how would it then support the coach who needs to keep his or her eyes on the athletes? What lessons in this testing enivronment could be applied to applied learning for others 'in the field' on an oil rig, in a battle zone, a farm or civil engineering project?]]></description>
